RACE.RACE_TEXT: AIKEN RACE 2 2 1/16M Hurdle CR: N/A. Maiden Special Weight Purse 15000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $20,000 OR LESS ON THE FLAT, OR OVER FENCES. Four-year-olds, 146 lbs.; older, 154 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CROSS BORDER opened clear to dictate terms toward the inside, dug in to meet the challenge leaving the final turn, was kept to task and gamely led throughout. BE YOURSELF tracked off of the inside, came under a ride leaving the final bend, took dead aim off of the last jump but was unable to best the determined winner. MISSION BRIEF was forwardly placed, hustled along in traffic, was within striking distance entering the stretch, but lacked the needed late response. THOMOND PARK settled in hand, mounted a mild advance between rivals, but failed to seriously threaten. POINT OF GRACE failed to make headway. WORLD OF FOOLS failed to respond. KING BUBBLE (IRE) made a middle move, loomed a danger on the backstretch, faltered leaving the final turn, fell over jump eight but walked off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AIKEN RACE 3 2 1/8M Hurdle CR: N/A. Handicap Purse 20000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH ARE RATED 110 OR LOWER. The highest rated horse will be assigned 158 lbs. with all other weights adjusted accordingly based on the current ratings. Minimum weight 140 lbs., not including a pprentice allowances.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HIGH MOUNTE (IRE) settled in hand, ranged up four wide into the final turn, poked his head in front entering the stretch, shook clear off of the next to last jump and widened. ANTICIPATING stalked the pace outside, bid between horses leaving the final turn, kept on well but was unable to match strides with the winner. HOOROO (IRE) was unhurried, ranged up in traffic, continued on willingly through the lane but settled for the minor award. YANKEE DOODLE BOY was unhurried, came four wide and improved position. JUNONIA was forwardly placed toward the inside, but faltered leaving the final turn and faded. CAPTAIN MIDDLETON (IRE) was hustled along in contention, but lacked a response when called upon. SENOR SEVILLE contended to the final turn and dropped out. THREE O ONE opened clear to set the pace, was collared on the final turn, came up empty once headed, fell off of the last jump but walked off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AIKEN RACE 4 2 1/16M Hurdle CR: N/A. Maiden Special Weight Purse 25000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Four-year-olds, 146 lbs.; older, 154 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SEISMIC WAVE stalked the pace toward the inside, got through to make his bid entering the stretch, came to level terms off of the last jump, came out under lefthanded urging, bumped FINDING FREEDOM soundly, was straightened away and edged clear. FINDING FREEDOM opened clear to set the pace, was collared nearing the final jump, was headed and bumped when the winner came out, was carried out nearing the wire and grudgingly gave in. CARL TIMOTHY was allowed to settle, came up empty on the final turn and retreated. SUMMER ANTHEM showed little. GIRL DAD tracked three wide, launched a bold bid entering the stretch, drew even nearing the last jump, fell off of the last jump but walked off. The jockey of FINDING FREEDOM lodged an objection against SEISMIC WAVE for alleged interference inside the final jump, but following the Stewards review there was no change to the order of finish.

ENTRY.COMMENT: allowed to settle, empty final turn, retreated

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AIKEN RACE 5 2 1/8M Hurdle CR: N/A. Handicap Purse 30000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH ARE RATED 120 OR LOWER. The highest rated horse will be assigned 158 lbs. with all other weights adjusted accordingly based on the current ratings. Minimum weight 140 lbs., not including a pprentice allowances.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WEST NEWTON (GB) opened clear to dictate terms, jumped inward hitting the wing on the last jump, briefly relinquished the lead, dug in once straightened and kicked clear. UCO VALLEY (IRE) settled in hand, moved up toward the inside to make his bid, inherited a brief lead when the winner veered in off of the last jump, continued on well but was unable to match strides the winner. DECISIVE TRIUMPH tracked three wide, weakened slightly during the drive and settled for the minor award. JIMMY P failed to respond. The jockey of UCO VALLEY (IRE) lodged an objection for alleged interference going into the final two jumps, but following the Stewards review there was no change to the order of finish. OUT OF AN ABUNDANCE OF CAUTION THE STEWARDS ELIMINATED THE FINAL JUMP.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: THE INSIDER (IRE) opened clear to control the tempo, dug in to meet the challenge entering the stretch, repelled both foes and kicked away.
